---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Projects — Barney Pinkerton">
  <div class="page-content">
    <h1>Projects</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">A selection of technical projects involving machine learning, dashboard analytics, and predictive modelling. Each card includes a short description, a skills snapshot, and a link to explore the full work.</p>

    <div class="card reveal">
      <h2>Evaluating Shazam-Style Fingerprinting and CLAP Audio Embeddings Under Degraded Conditions</h2>
      <div class="card-meta">NYU Group Project · Deep Learning · 2026</div>
      <p>Benchmarks two fundamentally different audio retrieval approaches – Shazam's deterministic landmark fingerprinting and LAION-CLAP neural embeddings – against a degraded audio dataset of 17,982 files derived from the GTZAN corpus. Tests cover additive noise (white, crowd, street at 0/10/20 dB SNR) and musical transforms (pitch shift ±1–3 semitones, lo-fi bandpass filtering). Key finding: Shazam and CLAP Music both collapse on pitch-shift, while CLAP General – a generalist model not designed for music – proves the most robust of the three.</p>

      <button class="read-btn desktop-only" data-src="/notebooks/analysis.html">▶&nbsp; View notebook inline</button>
      <a class="mobile-link mobile-only" href="/notebooks/analysis.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View notebook →</a>
      <div class="reader-frame desktop-only"></div>

      <div class="skills-list">
        <span class="skill-tag">Python</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">LAION-CLAP</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">PyTorch</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Librosa</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Scikit-learn</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">DSP · Spectrogram Analysis</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Audio Augmentation</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Cosine Similarity</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Evaluation Pipelines</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Jupyter Notebooks</span>
      </div>
      <a href="https://github.com/barneypinkerton/Shazam-CLAP-Embedding-Analysis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="card-link">View project on GitHub →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card reveal">
      <h2>Discogs Recommendation Model</h2>
      <div class="card-meta">Personal · Machine Learning · 2025</div>
      <p>A personalised vinyl recommender built using the full Discogs catalog. It runs a five-stage pipeline: ingesting the monthly Discogs data dump, syncing my collection and wantlist via the API, generating a 50k candidate pool leveraging label family graphs and artist/style affinity, ranking by metadata score, then re-ranking the top 300 using Essentia EffNet audio embeddings sourced from YouTube to find records that genuinely sound like my digital collection. Hard caps on community haves/wants keep results underground and hopefully cheap.</p>
      <div class="skills-list">
        <span class="skill-tag">Python</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">SQLite</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Discogs API</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">ETL Pipeline Design</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Graph-based Affinity Scoring</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Essentia EffNet Audio Embeddings</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Cosine Similarity</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">yt-dlp · ffmpeg</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Claude Code</span>
      </div>
      <button class="read-btn desktop-only" data-src="/notebooks/vinyl-profile.html">▶&nbsp; View collection profile</button>
      <a class="mobile-link mobile-only" href="/notebooks/vinyl-profile.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View collection profile →</a>
      <div class="reader-frame"></div>
      <a href="https://github.com/barneypinkerton/discogs-ml" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="card-link">View project on GitHub →</a>
    </div>

    <div class="card reveal">
      <h2>Apple Music Listening Analytics Dashboard</h2>
      <div class="card-meta">Personal · Data Visualisation · 2025</div>
      <p>A Tableau Public (i.e free tier with limited functionality) dashboard visualising my listening habits across songs, artists, albums, and genres. Includes parameters, ranking logic, calculated fields, and an integrated UX-focused layout for fun/dynamic analysis – happy clicking!</p>

      <div class="tableau-wrap desktop-only">
        <div id="viz_apple_music" style="position:relative; width:100%;"></div>
      </div>
      <a class="mobile-link mobile-only" href="https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/barnaby.pinkerton/viz/AppleMusicDashboard_17647709521790/AppleMusicDashboard?publish=yes" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View dashboard on Tableau Public →</a>

      <div class="skills-list">
        <span class="skill-tag">Tableau</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Calculated Fields · LODs</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Python ETL</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Time-based Filtering</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Dashboard UX Design</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Interactive Storytelling</span>
      </div>
      <a href="https://public.tableau.com/app/profile/barnaby.pinkerton/viz/AppleMusicDashboard_17647709521790/AppleMusicDashboard?publish=yes" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="card-link">Open full dashboard in Tableau Public →</a>

      <div class="analysis-section">
        <h3 class="analysis-title">Story time / Analysis</h3>

        <div class="analysis-block">
          <h4 class="analysis-subtitle">October 2025</h4>
          <p class="analysis-copy">
            Just after I moved to NYC, I started collecting my Apple Music listening data at the beginning of October, and I find it quite apt that my most listened to song for that month
            was 'Moving Out' by Vacations. A song about leaving home by a band from my hometown of Newcastle, Australia seems quite appropriate for that point in my life. It also looks like
            I mainly listened to this track on Sundays and Thursdays (Sunday listening to beat the gloomy end of the weekend homesickness followed by Thursday listening to get amped for the coming weekend in my new home?).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="analysis-block">
          <h4 class="analysis-subtitle">March 2026</h4>
          <p class="analysis-copy">
            This one is quite funny — my friends and I went and saw the Australian band Sticky Fingers late March at the Brooklyn Paramount. Clearly after that show all I could listen to
            for the rest of the month was their 2013 breakout hit 'Learn to Fly'. 
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="analysis-block">
          <h4 class="analysis-subtitle">April 2026</h4>
          <p class="analysis-copy">
            The return of Babyfather (one of Dean Blunt's many side projects) clearly had me obsessed. I inhaled 'icl' 100+ times in the last half of April alone. Whilst the song is aided by
            being roughly 2 minutes long, its instantly catchy beat made it hard to break the loop. April was also the month I discovered bar italia and completed a round trip to Australia in 
            under a week, where both outbound and return flights were on Monday, meaning there was lots of spare time flying to get into some new music.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card reveal">
      <h2>Term Deposit Subscription Prediction Model</h2>
      <div class="card-meta">Personal · Predictive Modelling · 2024</div>
      <p>A supervised machine learning classifier predicting customer conversion for term deposit campaigns. Includes preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, and evaluation (ROC-AUC, CV).</p>
      <div class="skills-list">
        <span class="skill-tag">Python</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Pandas · NumPy · Seaborn</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Scikit-learn</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Feature Engineering</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">ROC-AUC · Cross-validation</span>
        <span class="skill-tag">Jupyter Notebooks</span>
      </div>
      <a href="https://github.com/barneypinkerton/termdeposit-ml/blob/main/td_ml_v2.ipynb" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="card-link">View project on GitHub →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  // Tableau embed
  (function () {
    var container = document.getElementById('viz_apple_music');
    if (!container) return;
    var w = 960;

    var obj = document.createElement('object');
    obj.className = 'tableauViz';
    obj.style.cssText = 'width:' + w + 'px;height:827px;flex-shrink:0;';

    var params = {
      host_url: 'https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.tableau.com%2F',
      embed_code_version: '3',
      site_root: '',
      name: 'AppleMusicDashboard_17647709521790/AppleMusicDashboard',
      tabs: 'no',
      toolbar: 'yes',
      animate_transition: 'yes',
      display_static_image: 'yes',
      display_spinner: 'yes',
      display_overlay: 'yes',
      display_count: 'yes',
      language: 'en-US',
      filter: 'publish=yes',
    };
    Object.entries(params).forEach(function ([k, v]) {
      var p = document.createElement('param');
      p.name = k; p.value = v;
      obj.appendChild(p);
    });
    container.appendChild(obj);

    var s = document.createElement('script');
    s.src = 'https://public.tableau.com/javascripts/api/viz_v1.js';
    document.body.appendChild(s);
  })();

  // Notebook inline toggle
  document.querySelectorAll('.read-btn').forEach(function (btn) {
    btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
      var frame = btn.closest('.card').querySelector('.reader-frame');
      if (frame.children.length === 0) {
        var iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
        iframe.src = btn.dataset.src;
        iframe.style.cssText = 'display:block;width:100%;height:85vh;min-height:600px;border:none;border-radius:8px;box-shadow:0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);margin-top:14px;';
        frame.appendChild(iframe);
        btn.textContent = '▼  Close notebook';
      } else {
        frame.innerHTML = '';
        btn.textContent = '▶  View notebook inline';
      }
    });
  });

  // Scroll reveal
  var cards = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  cards.forEach(function (el, i) {
    el.style.transitionDelay = (i * 0.08) + 's';
  });
  var obs = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
    entries.forEach(function (e) {
      if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); obs.unobserve(e.target); }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.08, rootMargin: '0px 0px -40px 0px' });
  cards.forEach(function (el) { obs.observe(el); });
</script>

<style>
  .page-content {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1.5rem 3rem 4rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #0f172a;
  }

  .page-intro {
    color: #64748b;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .card {
    background: #fff;
    border-left: 5px solid #475569;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 28px 32px 22px;
    margin-bottom: 36px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.28s ease, box-shadow 0.28s ease, border-color 0.28s ease;
  }

  .card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    box-shadow: 0 10px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.11);
    border-color: #334155;
  }

  .card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 4px;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #0f172a;
  }

  .card-meta {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 0.82em;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .card p {
    color: #334155;
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .skills-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin: 4px 0 24px;
  }

  .skill-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #f1f5f9;
    color: #334155;
    border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .card:hover .skill-tag {
    background: #e2e8f0;
    border-color: #94a3b8;
  }

  .card-link {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #475569;
    text-decoration: none;
    position: relative;
  }

  .card-link::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -1px;
    left: 0;
    width: 0;
    height: 1.5px;
    background: currentColor;
    transition: width 0.25s ease;
  }

  .card-link:hover::after { width: 100%; }

  .tableau-wrap {
    margin: 16px 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  /* Scroll reveal */
  .reveal {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(36px);
    transition: opacity 0.55s ease, transform 0.55s ease;
  }
  .reveal.visible {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }

  .read-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    background: none;
    border: 1.5px solid #cbd5e1;
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 6px 16px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #475569;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .read-btn:hover {
    border-color: #475569;
    color: #0f172a;
    background: #f1f5f9;
  }

  .reader-frame iframe {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 14px;
    width: 100%;
    height: 85vh;
    min-height: 600px;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .mobile-link {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #475569;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .mobile-link:hover { color: #1e293b; }

  .analysis-section {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  }

  .analysis-title {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #0f172a;
    margin: 0 0 20px;
  }

  .analysis-block {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .analysis-subtitle {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #475569;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }

  .analysis-copy {
    color: #334155;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .mobile-only { display: none; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-content { padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem; }
    .desktop-only { display: none !important; }
    .mobile-only { display: inline-block; }
  }
</style>
